TY  - JOUR
TI  - Decision and Horizon Rules for Stochastic Planning Problems: A Linear Example
AU  - Charnes, Abraham
AU  - Drèze, Jacques
AU  - Miller, Merton
AB  - [Analytic decision rules and horizon rules are developed for the warehousing problem. A stochastic warehousing problem is defined and solved, first by backwards induction, then by means of a forward working algorithm. The influence of holding costs and discount rates on forecasting horizons is illustrated.]
